tweet: We know COVID-19 has exacerbated domestic violence in our state. At the same time, RI has seen a reduction in federal Victims of Crime Act funding since its peak in 2018. tweet: Today we honor the nearly 21,000 brave Rhode Islanders who served in Vietnam and we remember the over 200 who did not return home. Our state will always be deeply grateful for their service and sacrifice. #VietnamVeteransDay

name: Governor Dan McKee
tweet: Great jobs news this month for Rhode Island: the state’s unemployment rate has fallen below 4% for the first time since March 2020.   Plus, Rhode Island-based jobs are up 3,200 over the month – recouping all the jobs lost in January and more.  Let’s keep our momentum going.
